Class Drink

java.lang.Object
Drink
public class Drink extends Object
Represents a drink item in a customer's order.

The Drink class stores detailed information about a specific beverage ordered by a customer, including its size, ice level, sweetness levels, quantity, price, and any toppings and it's associated action.

    • Drink

      public Drink(int orderID, int beverageInfoID, String drinkName, int quantity, String iceLevel, String sweetnessLevel, String size, double price, String topping, String action)
      Creates a Drink object with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      orderID - the ID of the order this drink is associated with
      beverageInfoID - the unique ID of the beverage information record
      drinkName - the name of the drink
      quantity - the amount requested for this drink to be made
      iceLevel - the ice level preference
      sweetnessLevel - the sweetness level preference
      size - the size of the drink
      price - the price of the drink
      topping - the topping added to the drink
      action - the action associated with the topping to this drink
